          "username": "darop"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-06-17 10:31:50.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> do not change the copyright of existing files. you can put the\n > copyrights only on new files you created and there is \n > justification for it.\n > \n > why did you upgraded the jetty version? is there a functionality\n > you need from  the new version?\n\nThe upgrade is needed because of the jetty version used in the project (9.4.11.v20180605), which is listed as vulnerable according to \"Dublin SDC Security/Vulnerability Report\" document: https://wiki.onap.org/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=64004607\nAbout license header - according to this document : https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Rules+for+implementing+FOSS+in+a+project :\nAs indicated in Apache Version 2, Section 4.b, in case multiple companies are contributing, you must make it clear the file has been changed.\nThe easiest way is to simply add your company copyright after the original ones. \nIn case multiple companies are contributing, add each and every contributing companies.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
